Description: Real Estate CrowdFunding Platform
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Forefund leverages the United States JOBS Act to create a marketplace that seeks to put pre-screened investment deals in front of investors, and connects real estate entrepreneurs with financing that they might not find through old-school networking. For investors, the ForeFund platform curates real estate deals and real market data you need to faciliate sound investment decision making. Investors can get to know well-established real estate professionals and review their projects and profiles to make informed investment decisions based on market intelligence. They're also able to see the projects that aren’t doing as well; this transparency is something that has been widely available in everything from restaurants to stocks, but because of government regulations has been completely lacking in real estate investing. With the new JOBS act that all changes. Additionally, over time, being able to make smaller investments across a larger pool of properties allows investors to achieve greater diversification with their capital.  For real estate entrepreneurs, ForeFund exposes projects to a pool of potential investors quickly and easily. For larger projects, Entrepreneurs can leverage a team of professional marketers, putting years of experience with search, social, local and mobile media marketing to work to generate guaranteed investor leads and engagement in investments. With this widespread access to capital Real Estate entrepreneurs can focus on what you do best, finding great real estate projects and turning them into reality.  ForeFund is headquartered in sunny Venice Beach, California.

Description: Ability Connection Texas (ACT) has been providing vital care and support to people with disabilities for over 61 years.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Ability Connection Texas was founded on June 15th, 1953 as United Cerebral Palsy Association (UCPA) of Dallas County. Initially UCP offered a sheltered workshop for adults with cerebral palsy and in 1957 added day care and pre-school classes for children with cerebral palsy. Adult services were located in a church on McKinney Avenue and children’s services were housed in the basement of Highland Park United Methodist Church on Mockingbird Lane. In 1959 UCP joined United Way.  The 1960’s saw an era of growth in mission and capabilities when both children and adults programs came together in a facility located on Core Street. Shortly after this relocation, UCPA’s leadership realized that the number of people it was serving had outgrown the new location and funds were raised to build a new facility located at Anson and Parwelk that would accommodate administrative offices and all UCP programs. In 1975 additional space for programming was acquired and the adult program was moved to a nearby location to better care for the individuals UCP was serving.

Description: WholeLife Companies is a real estate developer and operator of active adult luxury class A rental communities.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: WholeLife Companies is a real estate developer and operator of active adult  luxury class A rental communities and  was  created around an innovative approach to addressing the issues of happiness, health, longevity and the preservation of wealth for today’s active adults. WholeLife has merged the latest designs, models and concepts from around the world into an intelligent community development program. The Company is developing luxury rental living communities integrating the concepts and practices of a healthy and enriching lifestyle into the creation of the community. The communities are designed to provide single-level, mid-rise and high-rise rental properties with the look of upscale homes and to offer a fitness center, pool, game room, concierge services and other community and personal services. Healthy living services, such as fitness evaluations, fitness instructors, wellness consultants, nutritionists, speakers and classes will also be available. The monthly rental fee is intended to include all the services and facilities. WholeLife Companies Subsidiaries include Wholelife Development, Wholelife Management, Wholelife Properties & Wholelife Franchise Company. WholeLife Development LLC is responsible for site selection, planning, design, entitlement and construction of projects either for WholeLife Properties, LLC or, under contract, to third parties.  WholeLife Management, LLC will provide both asset management and property management services for all the development and concierge WholeLife communities.   WholeLife Properties, LLC is the subsidiary of the Company that serves as the managing member of each of the project level single purpose limited liability companies created for each project. WholeLife Franchising, serves as a franchising arm of the Company.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Financial Services, Lending and Investments, Real Estate
